Title: Unpaid Labour in Productive Capacity
Description: The Productive Capacity Theory of Money framework begins with a simple observation: when you receive an employment letter, your relationship with the financial system transforms overnight. Banks that wouldn't lend you a dollar suddenly want to give you hundreds of thousands. Credit card companies compete for your business. Mortgage lenders calculate exactly how much house you can afford, typically three to four times your annual salary.
